summary: This is a brief email from the chambers of Judge Alison J. Nathan to counsel in the case US v. Maxwell (20cr330), transmitting a court order issued on November 30, 2021, and indicating the court will discuss sealing the order with the parties the following day.

persons.name: Nathan NYSD Chambers
persons.context: Sender of the email transmitting a court order in the US v. Maxwell case.

persons.name: Alison J. Nathan
persons.context: The Honorable Judge whose chambers sent the email and who issued the order to be discussed.

events.title: Court Order Issued
events.description: An order was issued by the Court in the case US v. Maxwell (20cr330).

events.title: Discussion on Sealing Order
events.description: The Court plans to discuss with the parties whether there is any basis to seal the order issued on November 30, 2021.

keyFacts: The document is an email from Judge Alison J. Nathan's chambers regarding case 20cr330, US v. Maxwell.
An order was issued by the court on November 30, 2021, and transmitted to counsel on December 1, 2021.
The court indicated it would discuss the potential sealing of this order with the parties the following day.
